The paper deals with the design of hybrid precoding/combiner for millimeter-wave massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The proposed solution involves the use of principal component analysis (PCA), which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the optimization of spectral efficiency (SE) and energy efficiency (EE), which are topics related to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the design of subarrays, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
